Before launch:
1.) Rename the package
2.) Create the beta community and add the beta link (make private for now)
3.) Add the community link to play store description, XDA description, and get help settings.

Launch Day:
1.) Put the app on the market for $0.99
2.) Create the XDA thread while waiting for the app to go live
3.) Make the Google+ beta community public
4.) After it is live:
	a.) Make the beta community public
	b.) Finish the XDA thread
	c.) Post on Google+
5.) Post on the Sliding Messaging page about its future
6.) Add the XDA thread to the play store description, and get help settings
7.) Make the first update with the xda link added
